{"id": "EUVD-2024-44730", "enisaUuid": "c44ee27e-d9a8-3dc8-bb3b-cba8594756e5", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nbtrfs: fix uninitialized pointer free in add_inode_ref()\n\nThe add_inode_ref() function does not initialize the \"name\" struct when\nit is declared.  If any of the following calls to \"read_one_inode()\nreturns NULL,\n\n\tdir = read_one_inode(root, parent_objectid);\n\tif (!dir) {\n\t\tret = -ENOENT;\n\t\tgoto out;\n\t}\n\n\tinode = read_one_inode(root, inode_objectid);\n\tif (!inode) {\n\t\tret = -EIO;\n\t\tgoto out;\n\t}\n\nthen \"name.name\" would be freed on \"out\" before being initialized.\n\nout:\n\t...\n\tkfree(name.name);\n\nThis issue was reported by Coverity with CID 1526744.", "datePublished": "2024-10-29T00:50:31", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-03T22:25:21", "baseScore": 7.8, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/12cf028381aa19bc38465341512c280256e8d82d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e11ce03b58743bf1e096c48fcaa7e6f08eb75dfa", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a941f3d5b1469c60a7e70e775584f110b47e0d16", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/66691c6e2f18d2aa4b22ffb624b9bdc97e9979e4", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-50088", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/01/msg00001.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-50088"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "093cca31-8f54-3930-9a28-ea59b8b906ea", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12"}, {"id": "13885d7d-9304-3a0f-83c2-cfc908709227", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "69358303-02b7-3a48-8d40-493d51a6151a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.2"}, {"id": "93063ef9-bf9b-321f-962a-d20c8895f19d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1cf474cd474bc5d3ef63086ffd009a87a5b7bb2e <12cf028381aa19bc38465341512c280256e8d82d"}, {"id": "ae08